Payom Building Its Largest Solar-Power Plant in Northern Germany

-- B y   S t e f a n   N i c o l a
-- 
2011-10-19T08:57:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-19/payom-building-its-largest-solar-power-plant-in-northern-germany.html
Payom Solar AG (P1Y) , a developer of
projects that generate power from the sun, started building its
largest photovoltaic plant in the northern German state of  Lower
Saxony .  The 4.4-megawatt plant in Oldenburg was financed with
proceeds from the issuance of a corporate bond and will start
operating before year-end, Cologne, Germany-based Payom said
today on its website.  The company will also develop projects to be built in the
first quarter of next year, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stefan Nicola in Berlin at 
 snicola2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
